"title": "9411: heaven, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9411",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture refers to heaven as God's habitation but also uses the term as an alternative for God himself.</p>\n<h2>Heaven as God's habitation</h2>\n<h3>It is the place where he dwells</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:15\">DEU 26:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:17\">GEN 28:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:21\">2CH 6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:2\">ECC 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:6\">REV 13:6</a></p>\n<h3>It is insufficient as God's dwelling-place</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:27\">1KI 8:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:18\">2CH 6:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps113:5-Ps113:6\">PSA 113:5–113:6</a></p>\n<h2>Heaven as the place of God's throne</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps11:4\">PSA 11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:9-Exod24:11\">EXO 24:9–24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:19\">1KI 22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:15\">ISA 63:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:9\">DAN 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:34\">MAT 5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:22\">MAT 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:49\">ACT 7:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:1\">ISA 66:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:1-Rev4:6\">REV 4:1–4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:11\">REV 20:11</a></p>\n<h2>Heaven as God's vantage point</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:13\">PSA 33:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps53:2\">PSA 53:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:19-Ps102:20\">PSA 102:19–102:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:2\">ECC 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Heaven as an alternative term for God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:18\">LUK 15:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:11\">MAT 8:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:11\">MAT 13:11</a> <em>Matthew is writing especially for Jews who, out of reverence, tried to avoid using the word “God”. <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:11\">Mk 4:11</a> and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:10\">Lk 8:10</a> prefer “kingdom of God”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:19\">MAT 16:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:18\">MAT 18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:25\">MAT 21:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:30\">MRK 11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:4\">LUK 20:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:27\">JHN 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a></p>\n<h2>Heaven and the sovereignty of God</h2>\n<h3>Heaven is the place of God's rule</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:26\">DAN 4:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:6\">PSA 45:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:19\">PSA 103:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24\">ACT 17:24</a></p>\n<h3>God's voice from heaven speaks with divine authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:36\">DEU 4:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:31\">DAN 4:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:28\">JHN 12:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:17-2Pet1:18\">2PE 1:17–1:18</a></p>\n<h2>Heaven glimpsed by human eyes</h2>\n<h3>At the baptism of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:10\">MRK 1:10</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16\">MAT 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:21-Luke3:22\">LUK 3:21–3:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:32\">JHN 1:32</a></p>\n<h3>In visions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:56\">ACT 7:56</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:2-2Cor12:4\">2CO 12:2–12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:1\">REV 4:1</a></p>\n<h2>Prayer addressed to God in heaven</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:30\">1KI 8:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:15\">DEU 26:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:27\">2CH 30:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4\">NEH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:6\">PSA 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:8\">REV 5:8</a></p>\n<h2>The association of oaths with heaven</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:22\">MAT 23:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:3\">GEN 24:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:7\">DAN 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:34\">MAT 5:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:12\">JAS 5:12</a></p>\n<h2>The place of Jesus Christ in heaven</h2>\n<h3>His pre-existence in heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:38\">JHN 6:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:13\">JHN 3:13</a></p>\n<h3>His ascension into heaven after his resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:51\">LUK 24:51</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:19\">MRK 16:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:20\">EPH 1:20</a></p>\n<h3>His place is now with God the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>His second coming will be from heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31\">MAT 25:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:11\">ACT 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:10\">1TH 1:10</a></p>\n<h2>The new heaven</h2>\n<h3>The new heaven completely replaces the old</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1\">REV 21:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:17\">ISA 65:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:22\">ISA 66:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:13\">2PE 3:13</a></p>\n<h3>The new Jerusalem is divinely created in heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:5\">ISA 2:2–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:16\">HEB 11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:14\">HEB 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:12\">REV 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:10\">REV 21:10</a></p>\n<h3>Fulness of life in heaven is wholly sustained by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:22-Rev21:23\">REV 21:22–21:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:1-Rev22:2\">REV 22:1–22:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:1\">ISA 55:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:8-Ezek47:9\">EZK 47:8–47:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:12\">EZK 47:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:38-John7:39\">JHN 7:38–7:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a></p>",
